Kvaerner wins NOK 170 mln ferry deal . Anglo - Norwegian construction and engineering group Kvaerner ASA said on Thursday its Kvaerner Fjellstrand shipyard in Norway had won a contract to build a high speed passenger and car ferry catamaran from Express Ferries Ltd . The deal was worth around 170 million crowns , Kvaerner said in a statement . The 60 metre JumboCat will be used between Helsinki in Finland and Tallinn in Estonia . It was due for delivery in April , 1998 . The aluminium vessel will carry up to 430 passengers and 52 cars . It is the second such ferry to be built at the yard . Kvaerner said the contract included an option for a second vessel for delivery in spring , 1999 . - - Oslo newsroom , + 47 22 42 50 41 
